Light morph has nearly pure white undersides of wings and base of tail. Dark morph is nearly all brown with light gray trailing edge of wings.

Highly variable-plumaged hawk with three easily distiguishable color morphs. Light morph is brown with a white belly, a warm rusty brown with a white face. Intermediate has a dark breast, rusty belly and white at base of bill. Dark morph is nearly all dark brown with a rusty color low on belly.

Large bird with obvious red head and legs. In flight, the wings appear two-toned: black leading edge with gray on the trailiing edge and tip. The tip of wings end in fingure-like projections. Long squared tail. Ivory bill.

A glossy black bird, reminiscent of a red-winged blackbird. Chocolate brown head with a pointed, sharp gray bill
A mostly black bird with dirty red-brown sides and white belly. multiple white spots on wings and sides. Long black tail with a white tip. Rich red eyes.

Colors: Black, Green, Purple, White, Yellow, Gray
Description: Overall glossy black, shining green in diect light. Head more purple than green. Bright white or pale yellow eyes. Winter plumage can be dull gray to black.
Large black bird with a lemon yellow head, chest and nape of neck. Black mask and a gray bill. White wing patches.

Slate gray to black all over, white bill with dark band near ti. Green legs and feet. A small white patch near the base of the tail. Prominate red eyes, with a small red patch above bill between eyes.
Large all-black water bird with long snake-like neck. A long yellow orange bill with a hooked tip.

A small woodpecker with an all-white belly, black-and-white spotted wings, a black line running through the eyes, a short black bill, a white stripe running down the back and red markon  the back of the head. Serveral small black spots along the sides of the white tail.
Short, stocky black bird with a large broad head, white wing patches and large bluish gray bill. Winter is black, brown, gray and white striped, with white wing patches.
Black-and-white pattern on the back in two rows. Red forhead, chin, and nape of neck.
More black than white with a red chin and bright yellow belly. Bold white stripes just above and below the eyes. White rump and wing patches flash when in flight.
Black-and-white woodpecker with a white belly, and black wings with rows of white spots. White stripe down back. Long black bill. Red mark on back of head.
Upper parts of the head, neck and back are black. Lower parts are white. Ridiculously long red-to-pink legs. Long black bill.

Colors: Black, White, Gray, Purple, Green, Yellow
Description: Appears mostly black with bold white sidesand gray back. Chest and head look nearly black, but head appears purple in direct sun. Bright yellow eyes.
Black and white back, white belly. A long, thin upturned bill and long gray legs. Head and neck rusty red during breeding, gray in the winter.
Crow-sized woodpecker with a black and bring red crest. Long gray bill with red mustache. White leading edge of the wings flashes brightly when flying.

A long-necked, nearly all-black water bird with white chin, neck, chest and belly. Long yellow bill and brighht red eyes. Dark crown extends around the eyes to base of bill. During winter, becomes light gray around eyes.
Aturquoise blue head, neck, back and tail. Cinnamon chest with cinnamon extending down flanks slightly. White belly. Two bold white wing bars. Non-breeding male has a spotty blue head and back.
Blue green in the spring and greener in fall. Appears to change color in direct sunlight. A white belly, a notched tail and pointed wing tips.

Colors: Blue, Black, Cinnamon, Red, Brown, White
Description: A sleek swallow with a blue black back, a cinnamon belly and a reddish brown chin. White spots on long forked tail.
Deep blue head, neck, back, wings, and tail. Rusty red chest and flanks.
An overall sky blue bird with a darker blue head, back, wings, tail and white lower belly. Thin black bill

Colors: Blue, Gray, White, Red, Brown, Black
Description: Large blue bird with a white belly. Broad blue gray breast band and a ragged crest that is raised and lowered at will. Large head with a long, thick black bill. A small white spot directly in front of red brown eyes. Black wing tips with slashes of white that flash when flying.
Rich, warm chestnut back and sides. Black crown and chin. White cheeks and sides of head. Gray wings and tail.
Small, thin, nearly camouflaged brown bird. White from chin to belly, White eyebrows. Long stiff tail. Thin curved bill.
Small gray brown sparrow with a clear gray chest, rusty crown, white eyebrows with a black eye line, thin gray black bill and two faint wing bars
A plain brown bird with a heavily streaked white chest.
A small all-brown bird with a lighter brown markings on tail and wings. Slightly curved brown bill. Often holds its tail erect.
A uniquely patterened swallow with a dark back, wings and cap. Distinctive tan-to-rust rump, cheeks and forehead.
Overall grayish brown with tinges of buffy brown on tail and wings. Gray back, often finely speckled with white. Belly and breast are light tan.
Gray crown with a black forehead, chin and throat. Warm cinnamon-brown body with a wash of rosy red, especially along flanks and rumps.
Light wash of crimson red, especially bright red crown, brown streaks on the back and wings, white belly.
All-brown bird with unique rust red, white and black head pattern. White breast with central gray spot. Gray rump and white edges to gray tail, as seen in flight.
A brown sparrow with a gray breast and a black-and-white striped crown. Small, in pink bill.
Plump brown sparrow with a gray head, back and rump. White chest and belly with rusty brown streaks. Rusty tail and wings.
Brown with a slightly ornage nape of neck. brown necklace. Yellow chin and forehead. Black spots near eyes, behind black bill. Two tiny "horns" on head can be hard to see.
Very sleek-looking gray-to-brown bird with pointed crest, light yellow belly and bandit-like mask. Tip of tail is bright yellow and the tips of wings look as if they have been dipped in red wax
Olive brown back. Long bill and long dull yellow legs. White line over eyes. Breeding plumage has black spots on a white chest and belly. Winter has a clear chest and belly.
Appears like an overgrown sparrow. Overall brown with lighter-colored chest and belly, prominent white eyebrows and a large two-toned bill.
A camouflaged brown and white bird with a white chin. A distinctive white band across wings and tail, seen only in flight.
An upland shorebird with two black bands around the neck like a necklace. A brown back and white belly. Bright reddish orange rump, visable only in flight.
Small brown water bird with a black chin and black ring around a thick, chicken-like ivory bill. Puffy white patch under tail. Has an unmarkable brown bill during winter.
A chestnut head witha  dark green patch in back of eyes extending down to nape of neck and outlined in white. Gray body with a butter yellow tail. Green speculum.
Deep cinnamon head, neck and belly. Light brown back. Dark gray bill. Deep red eyes. Non-breeding male is overall brown with red tinge.
Brown chicken-like bird with long squared tail. Wide banc near tip of tail. Is able to fan tail like a turkey. Tuft of feathers on head stand like a crown. Black ruffs on sides of neck.
Highly ornamented with a green head and crest patterned with white and black, rusty chest, white belly and red eyes.

A brown duck with a rounded head, a long pointed tail and short, black-tipped grayish bill. Obvious white cap. Deep green patch starting behind eyes, streaking down neck. White belly and wing linings, seen in flight. Non-breeding lacks white caps, green patch.

Colors: Brown, Black, Green, White, Blue, Rust
Description: Medium-sized brown duck speckled with black. Blue wing patch. An extrodinarily large spoon-shaped bill. Iridescent green head, rusty sides and white breast
A mottled brown chicken-like bird with a gray belly. Yellow-orange patch of skin above the eyes. Tail is dark brown and squared off.
Robust brown "horned" owl. Bright yellow eyes and V-shaped white throat resembling a necklace. Horizontal barring on chest
Cinnamon brown with an extremely long, down-curved bill. Long bluish legs. Darker cinnamon wings linings, seen in flight.

A slender, elegant duck with a brown head, wihte neck, gray body and extremely long narrow black tail. Gray bill. Non-breeding has a pale brown head that lacks the clear demarcation between the brown head and white neck. Lacks long tail feathers.

Colors: Green, White, Brown, Rust, Chestnut, Gray, Yellow, Orange
Description: Large bulbous green head, white necklace, rust brown or chestnut, combination of gray and white on the sides, yellow bill, orange legs and feet.

Colors: Gold, Brown, White, Purple, Green, Blue, Red
Description: Golden brown body with a long tail. White ring around neck with  purple, green, blue, and red head.
Large, plump brown and bronze bird with striking blue and red bare head. Fan tail and long, straight black beard in center of chest. Spurs on legs.
Small, teardrop-shaped green-to-gray bird. Two white wing bars. Hidden ruby-colored crown. White eye-ring.
Tiny gray-blue black bird with gray-brown crown. Creamy chest with a lighter chin. A relatively short tail, large head and loong bill.
Overall gray with a black cap, chin nd line through eyes. White eyebrows.
